storyDescription: At first I thought this unknown number was a total creeper, but then something sort of magical happened.

messages.text: are you up for a game?
I think you sent this txt to the wrong number
nonsense, madison.
i want to play with you :)
who is this? what game?
this is your best friend :D
uhh...no, it's not.
this isn't abby or sophie's number.
who are you?
why can't i see what number you're txting from?
lol, not one of your BFFs
i'm the best friend you've never met
i'm the one who is going to make wishes come true
i don't know who you are...
but you're being a total creeper
want to find out who i am?
we can play a game
no. stop texting me
i'm sorry.
i'm getting off on the wrong foot
what i really want to know is...
do you want to go to homecoming?
OMG
wait, really?
that's what this is?
you're super nice and smart...
and I think you should have a fun date for the dance ;)
alright, Mystery Man.
i get it.
what game do i have to play to find out who you are? :)
how about a scavenger hunt?
right now? i kind of have plans...
call sophie about your yoga class, and text me back afterwards
how do you know sophie and i are going to yoga?
i called sophie
she's feeling “sick” and has to cancel.
so sophie is in on this? i think i know who you are now...
oh, you do? :)
i have my hopes ;)
who do you think I am then?
i'm not telling :p
well, i guess you'll find out...ready for our scavenger hunt?
where do we start?
it's 3 things: something from a bargain bin, a penny that's been wished with, and something 15 and silver
oh wow. talk about cryptic
bargain bin...like at goodwill?
;D
lemme bike over there
i'll text you when I get there and need to know what I'm looking for
you'll know it when you see it ;)
OMG. I'M HERE. I FOUND IT.
Do you like it? :)
how did a BG Haute gown end up in the bargain bin????
it's still got the original tags in it and everything, but the thrift shop's selling it for $5!!!
i don't know who you are, but you're magical. i bought the dress
ready for your next surprise?
yeah. i've got to find a coin from like a wishing well?
maybe...
kids throw pennies in the fountain at the silver lake mall...does that count?
:D
OK. heading to the mall
so i'm at the fountain. i found a penny. i don't get it
wait for it ;)
WTF is going on
What's the matter? :/
Tanner Mooney just came out of game stop and saw me and we just sat and chatted for like 15 minutes at the fountain
he asked me to homecoming
don't you like tanner? i thought you were wishing he would ask you... :(
nobody knows that except for Sophie and Rachel
i thought YOU wanted to ask me out
i just wanted you to have a nice date
you're a total creeper. you put Tanner up to this?
what's going on?
WHO ARE YOU?
something 15 and silver
WTF does that mean
you're almost finished with the game
screw your game. you're freaking me out
don't freak out. i'm the best friend you've never met, remember?
you're a creep. do you even go to LHS?
15 and silver
STOP SAYING THAT
you'll have to figure it out if you want to know who i am
i may have forgoten to mention...you have to win the game to keep all the prizes
what does that mean?
the dress, the date...you have to win otherwise it goes away
what, you're going to steal my dress and get tanner to un-ask me?
maybe you'll lose the dress. or tear it.
maybe you get grounded before the dance.
maybe tanner's family forces him to visit his aunt that weekend
WTF you can't do that.
you're the one who said I was magical
something 15 and Silver
...is 15 an age?
no
is silver a name?
a name of something, not someone
does 15 and silver describe who you are?
no.
does it describe where you are?
smart girl ;)
are you out on the lake right now?
close...
is 15 a dock or a house number or something on silver lake?
not quite...
i'm biking to the lake now. maybe I'll figure it out on my way there
15TH STREET AND SILVER DRIVE
IT'S AN INTERSECTION
so smart! you win!
come find me
i'm waiting with prize number three :)
i'm on silver drive now. give me 5
OK, i'm here. i don't see you. are you in the woods?
you said you'd be here
this isn't just another stupid clue is it?
i'm not going to look for clues
you're freaking me out. there's NO ONE out here
if you're not even going to text me back, i'm leaving
you're not going to leave me
not after I just gave you the most beautiful dress you could wish for and the best homecoming date you could wish for.
then where are you?
check under the street sign
in all this grass?
i found a dorky clay thing. is this part of the game?
you win, madison
what is it? i don't get it
it's an oil lamp
go on, pick it up
you've still got one wish left

author.bio:
Author of THE NEVERLAND WARS, a YA fantasy novel and modern day continuation of the Peter Pan story, available for preorder now. Her other books, short stories, flash fiction, and poems can be found on audreygreathouse.com

Audrey Greathouse is a lost child in a perpetual footloose quest for her own post-adolescent Neverland. Originally from Seattle, she earned her BA in English literature online from Southern New Hampshire University while backpacking the west coast. A pianist, circus artist, fire-eater, street mime, swing dancer, and novelist, she has warn many hats as an artist and now resides in Silicon Valley's San Jose.
